cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MA, cs.AI 

The paper deals with a game-theoretic problem of Internet price war and proposes a variant of Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) to infer latent variables representing the preferences of customers and strategies of competitors. This suggests that the paper could belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.GT (Computer Science > Computer Science and Game Theory): as the paper deals with a game-theoretic problem, this sub-category is the most likely. 
- cs.LG (Computer Science > Machine Learning): as the paper proposes a variant of LDA, a popular machine learning technique, this sub-category is also likely. 
- cs.IR (Computer Science > Information Retrieval): as the paper deals with inferring latent variables from observable data, this sub-category is also possible. 
- cs.MA (Computer Science > Multiagent Systems): as the paper deals with the relationship between companies and customers in a competitive environment, this sub-category is also possible. 
- cs.AI (Computer Science > Artificial Intelligence): as the paper proposes a machine learning technique to solve a game-theoretic problem, this sub-category is also possible.
